Detailed Crash Investigation Supplement
(For review by the MSP Crash Team)




Section I. - Narrative

On 3/31/2023 at approximately 1441 Hrs, The Maryland State Police, Hagerstown Barracks were dispatched to respond to a single-vehicle collision, where the vehicle traveled from the roadway and struck a metal fence barrier for a Government data facility. Upon arrival, Troopers located a 2004 Jeep Cherokee (MD 56341M3), off the right shoulder of the roadway. The operator was located on the passenger side floorboard with a severe head injury and emergency services were immediately dispatched. The driver was identified as Matthew Wayne Wiles (Caucasian Male, 4/8/61) of Sharpsburg, MD. Due to the significance of the injury emergency personnel requested Aviation to respond, which prompted the Duty Officer to request a Reconstructionist to the scene. Cpl G.L. Baker #4702, of the Maryland State Police, Commercial Vehicle Enforcement Division responded to the scene of the collision and began processing the scene. Initial investigation showed the Jeep traveled approximately 300 feet from the roadway before colliding into a metal fence barrier located on the corner of MD Rt 632 and Rench Rd. Evidence at the scene showed the driver was not properly secured by his safety belt and after speaking with members of his family at the scene it was learned he has a history and is currently being treated for seizures. When observing the scene, no pre-impact braking or evidentiary markings were found. While processing the scene, The Maryland State Police, Hagerstown Barracks Duty Officer informed Cpl Baker, the victim in the collision's medical status was upgraded, and he was alert and talking. Cpl Baker finished processing the scene and responded to the barracks shortly afterward as of writing this report on 4/4/23. A medical re-evaluation form has been completed for the victim concerning his driver's license.

All events occurred in Washington County, Maryland.

Conclusion:

This case will be considered closed. The at-fault party in this case survived the crash and was treated and released from R Adams Cowley Shock Trauma Center in Baltimore, MD. Due to the circumstances of the collision, the offender was not charged with any traffic violations, but a Medical Re-Evaluation request was filed with the Maryland Motor Vehicle Administration.
